### Write Vitest Integration Test for Supabase User Signup and Profile Creation

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/www/_blog/2025-08-16-testing-for-vibe-coders-from-zero-to-production-confidence.mdx

This TypeScript/JavaScript integration test uses Vitest to verify the end-to-end functionality of Supabase user signup, including associated database triggers and Row Level Security. Before each test, it clears existing profiles. The test flow involves signing up a new user, asserting no errors, and then querying the `profiles` table to confirm that a corresponding profile row was automatically created, validating the entire authentication and database interaction sequence.

```tsx
import { expect, test, beforeEach } from 'vitest'
import { supabase } from './setup'

beforeEach(async () => {
  await supabase.from('profiles').delete().neq('id', '')
})

test('sign up creates a profile row via trigger', async () => {
  const email = `test-${Date.now()}@example.com`
  const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signUp({
    email,
    password: 'Pass1234!',
  })

  expect(error).toBeNull()
  expect(data.user?.email).toBe(email)

  const { data: profile } = await supabase
    .from('profiles')
    .select('*')
    .eq('id', data.user?.id)
    .single()

  expect(profile).toBeTruthy()
})
```

