### Test Row Level Security (RLS) for User Data Isolation in Supabase (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/www/_blog/2025-08-16-testing-for-vibe-coders-from-zero-to-production-confidence.mdx

This test verifies that Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) correctly prevents authenticated users from accessing data belonging to other users. It simulates two users signing up, one creating a post, and the other attempting to read that post, asserting that the second user receives no data.

```tsx
test('users cannot see each other\'s posts', async () => {
  const u1 = await supabase.auth.signUp({
    email: 'u1@test.com',
    password: 'pass'
  })
  const u2 = await supabase.auth.signUp({
    email: 'u2@test.com',
    password: 'pass'
  })

  await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({
    email: 'u1@test.com',
    password: 'pass'
  })
  const { data: post } = await supabase
    .from('posts')
    .insert({ title: 'secret' })
    .select()
    .single()

  await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({
    email: 'u2@test.com',
    password: 'pass'
  })
  const { data: rows } = await supabase
    .from('posts')
    .select()
    .eq('id', post!.id)

  expect(rows?.length ?? 0).toBe(0)
})
```

