### Verify Organization Editor RLS Restrictions (SQL)

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/local-development/testing/pgtap-extended.mdx

This test case authenticates as an 'org_editor' and attempts an unauthorized action (inserting a new member into `org_members`) to confirm that RLS policies correctly restrict editors from managing members. It uses `throws_ok` to assert that an RLS violation error occurs.

```sql
-- Test editor restrictions
select tests.authenticate_as('org_editor');
select throws_ok(
  $$
    insert into org_members (org_id, user_id, role)
    values (
      (select id from organizations limit 1),
      (select tests.get_supabase_uid('org_editor')),
      'viewer'
    )
  $$,
  '42501',
  'new row violates row-level security policy for table "org_members"',
  'Editor cannot manage members'
);
```

